definition: difference/discrepancy/to differ/error/to err/to make a mistake
to differ from/to fall short of/lacking/wrong/inferior/Taiwan pr. [cha1]
to adjust to a different time zone

sentences.english: I haven't recovered from jet lag yet.
Excuse me. What's the time difference betweeen Beijing and London?
sentences.chinese: 请问北京和伦敦的时差是多少？

sentences.english: Early flight to Nanchang so no time to worry about jet lag.
sentences.chinese: 赶早班飞机来南昌，没时间担心时差了。

sentences.english: What's the time difference between Beijng and London?
sentences.chinese: 北京和伦敦的时差是多少？

sentences.english: Unfortunately, because of the time difference. I can not look at each regular competitions are.
sentences.chinese: 遗憾的是，因为时差的问题，我不能每常比赛都看。

sentences.english: Maybe it's jet lag from yesterday.
sentences.chinese: 也许是你昨天倒时差的关系。

sentences.english: You must be tired for the time difference.
sentences.chinese: 我想您肯定是因为“时差病”而感到累了吧。

sentences.english: Social jet lag is described as the difference between biological time and external requirements.
sentences.chinese: 社会时差被描述为生物时间与外部要求之间的差异。

sentences.english: The problem of Jet Lag is one every international traveler comes across.
sentences.chinese: 时差反应是每一个国际旅行者可能遇到的问题。

sentences.english: Or maybe it's just that the jetlag is getting to me.
sentences.chinese: 或者也许只是时差对我的影响。

sentences.english: After I get over jet-lag, I'll call you.
sentences.chinese: 我倒过时差后给你打电话。

sentences.english: But I also feel bad because of the lower pressure and the jet lag.
sentences.chinese: 但是我还是因为低压和时差而感到难受。

sentences.english: It took me a week to get over my jet lag.
sentences.chinese: 我花了一个礼拜才把时差调过来。

sentences.english: Cross-correlation in passive TDOA locating is discussed.
sentences.chinese: 研究了互相关法在无源时差定位系统中的应用。

sentences.english: Well, you must be tired after a long trip, and you have to get over the jet-lag.
sentences.chinese: 嗯，长途旅行之后您一定很累了，您还得倒时差呢。

sentences.english: On arrival at the hotel, feeling jet lagged, I went straight to sleep.
sentences.chinese: 我抵达旅馆后，因时差而感到疲倦，倒下就睡。
